Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve any larger @baby potatoes{500%grams}.

On a lined #baking tray{}, toss with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Roast on the top shelf of the oven, ~{15-20%minutes}.

After ~{20%minutes}, remove from the oven. Lightly crush each potato with the bottom of a #pan.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}. Sprinkle with @grated Italian style hard cheese{25%grams} and @Irish bacon lardons{100%grams}. Return to the top shelf of the oven until golden, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, mix together the @green pesto{1%sachet} and @mayo{2%sachets}.

In a separate #large bowl{}, mix together the @balsamic glaze{1%sachet}, @oil{1%tbsp}, @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. This is your dressing!

> Double the oil for 4p.

Trim the @baby gem{120%grams}, halve lengthways and thinly slice widthways.

Just before serving, toss the salad leaves through the balsamic dressing.

Trim and thinly slice the @scallion{1}.

== Chicken ==

Lay the @Irish chicken breast{320%grams} out on a #cutting board{}.

Place your hand flat on top of the chicken breast and slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Repeat with the other breast(s).

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging we use to keep it fresh.

Beat @egg{1} in a #medium bowl{}.

> Double the egg for 4p.

Add the @breadcrumbs{1%pack} to a separate #bowl{}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Dip the chicken first into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely coated.

Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

Place a #large pan{} over high heat with just enough @oil{to taste} to cover the bottom.

Once hot, lay the chicken into the pan, reduce the heat to medium-high and fry until golden brown and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Turn every ~{2-3%minutes} and adjust the heat if necessary.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pop the @brioche buns{2} into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: Cook in batches if the pan is too crowded.

== Assembly ==

When everything's ready, spread the pesto mayo over the cut side of the bun lids.

Top the bun bases with a handful of balsamic salad.

Load on the crumbed chicken, then sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Serve the remaining salad and cheesy bacon smashed potatoes alongside.

Sprinkle sliced scallion over the potatoes to finish.